{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.40",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 40,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 40",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 40 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:1",
      "text": "And the Lord said to Job:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:2",
      "text": "“Shall a faultfinder contend with the Almighty? He who argues with God, let him answer it.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:3",
      "text": "Then Job answered the Lord:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:4",
      "text": "“Behold, I am of small account; what shall I answer thee? I lay my hand on my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:5",
      "text": "I have spoken once, and I will not answer; twice, but I will proceed no further.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:6",
      "text": "Then the Lord answered Job out of the whirlwind:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:7",
      "text": "“Gird up your loins like a man; I will question you, and you declare to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:8",
      "text": "Will you even put me in the wrong? Will you condemn me that you may be justified?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:9",
      "text": "Have you an arm like God, and can you thunder with a voice like his?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:10",
      "text": "“Deck yourself with majesty and dignity; clothe yourself with glory and splendor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:11",
      "text": "Pour forth the overflowings of your anger, and look on every one that is proud, and abase him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:12",
      "text": "Look on every one that is proud, and bring him low; and tread down the wicked where they stand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:13",
      "text": "Hide them all in the dust together; bind their faces in the world below.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:14",
      "text": "Then will I also acknowledge to you, that your own right hand can give you victory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:15",
      "text": "“Behold, Behemoth, which I made as I made you; he eats grass like an ox.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:16",
      "text": "Behold, his strength in his loins, and his power in the muscles of his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:17",
      "text": "He makes his tail stiff like a cedar; the sinews of his thighs are knit together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:18",
      "text": "His bones are tubes of bronze, his limbs like bars of iron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:19",
      "text": "“He is the first of the works of God; let him who made him bring near his sword!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:20",
      "text": "For the mountains yield food for him where all the wild beasts play.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:21",
      "text": "Under the lotus plants he lies, in the covert of the reeds and in the marsh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:22",
      "text": "For his shade the lotus trees cover him; the willows of the brook surround him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:23",
      "text": "Behold, if the river is turbulent he is not frightened; he is confident though Jordan rushes against his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.40.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:24",
      "text": "Can one take him with hooks, or pierce his nose with a snare?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
